stay there so the CPS could investigate.

507
00:55:37,283 --> 00:55:38,307
Shit.

508
00:55:38,485 --> 00:55:40,851
Sure, I remember her.
Her sister had just died...

509
00:55:41,021 --> 00:55:43,080
...and one of the nurses
filled out a report.

510
00:55:43,256 --> 00:55:44,848
Right. Do you remember her mother?

511
00:55:45,025 --> 00:55:48,654
Was her mother there when the fire
started? It was during visiting hours?

512
00:55:48,828 --> 00:55:52,195
That wouldn't have made a difference.
The mother was there all the time.

513
00:56:09,149 --> 00:56:11,540
Excuse me. I'm looking for a student,
her name is Beth.

514
00:56:11,684 --> 00:56:13,510
She was supposed to be here
earlier today.

515
00:56:14,788 --> 00:56:15,812
Where are you?

516
00:56:16,089 --> 00:56:19,081
I think Marie Layton was in the hospital
when it burned down.

517
00:56:19,259 --> 00:56:21,056
I think that she might've died there.

518
00:56:21,227 --> 00:56:23,252
Impossible. All the bodies were identified.

519
00:56:23,430 --> 00:56:27,025
I know, but what if they didn't find her?
What if her body's still inside?

520
00:56:27,200 --> 00:56:31,967
<i>She was a sick woman, a child abuser.
What if her body is still inside...</i>

521
00:56:32,138 --> 00:56:34,902
...and her spirit's there,
moving through the phones...

522
00:56:35,075 --> 00:56:36,337
...attacking people?

523
00:56:38,378 --> 00:56:40,972
Okay, all right. Where are you?
I'll come get you.

524
00:56:41,881 --> 00:56:46,477
Well, here we are, miss, Saint Luke's.

525
00:56:46,653 --> 00:56:48,553
<i>What's left of it, anyway.</i>

526
00:56:48,692 --> 00:56:51,256
<i>Beth, no! Wait for me, all right?
I'm on my way.</i>

527
00:56:51,257 --> 00:56:53,452
Hurry, there's not much time.

